lly stop being the dominant shape."],[1026,"This is useful for Electron preload APIs, CLIs, API clients, docs search, and cache warmers where several callers can ask for the same thing at once."],[109,"This page is the short list of habits that keep tuple-based code clean under real production pressure."],[281,"This recipe is for the common \"do this for every item\" path: refresh every repo, fetch every avatar, resize every image, or inspect every file. The work is independent, but starting it all at once can make a user's machine or an upstream service miserable."],[346,"This recipe shows the shape Yieldless is best at: an HTTP request that validates input, performs a few pieces of I/O, retries the flaky part, and returns a normal JSON response."],[36,"This rule keeps the library easy to explain to engineers who did not build the original system."],[37,"Thrown exceptions are still useful for process-level failures and framework boundaries, but routine operational failures should stay explicit."],[1034,"Thrown operation failures are normalized into tuple errors."],[383,"Thrown task and mapper failures are normalized into tuple failures internally."],[1007,"Timeout failures use `TimeoutError` by default."],[89,"Timeouts and timers"],[117,"Timers without abort handling tend to outlive the work they were created for."],[861,"Total number of attempts including the first"],[489,"Trace spans"],[122,"Trace spans, request IDs, user sessions, or a transaction handle fit well."],[468,"Tracing shape"],[491,"Transaction handles"],[140,"Transform or chain tuples"],[881,"Transient database connection failures"],[435,"Trip only on dependency failures, not user input."],[163,"TTL/LRU caching with shared in-flight loads."],[440,"TTL/LRU tuple caches with in-flight load sharing."],[958,"Tuple adapters for safeParse(), parse(), safeParseAsync(), and parseAsync() style validators."],[199,"Tuple filesystem helpers and subprocess output capture."],[520,"Tuple helpers for required environment variables and schema-backed config parsing."],[663,"Tuple helpers for sync and async iterable workflows."],[196,"Tuple serialization and optional renderer-driven cancellation."],[716,"Tuple wrappers for Node filesystem work and child-process execution."],[363,"Tuple-aware parallel combinators that share cancellation."],[545,"Tuple-based error handling primitives."],[148,"Tuple-native `all()`, `race()`, and fixed-list `mapLimit()`."],[891,"Tuple-returning route handlers with HTTP error mapping."],[623,"Typed Electron IPC helpers that preserve tuple results across the process boundary."],[246,"TypeScript 5.5+ is the target baseline. The package is compiled with `isolatedDeclarations` enabled."],[512,"TypeScript enforces that the injected object satisfies `Deps` before the returned function can be called"],[547,"Typical use"],[987,"Typical use"],[916,"Unknown error"],[865,"Upper bound on the computed delay"],[808,"Use `acquireResource()` when cleanup must happen even if the body throws."],[385,"Use `all()` for a small, fixed set of independent tuple tasks."],[384,"Use `all()`, `race()`, and `mapLimit()` when the work is already tuple-native. Use `runTaskGroup()` when you want imperative fan-out and regular promise values."],[841,"Use `andThen()` when the second step depends on the first success value."],[811,"Use `await using` when the TypeScript target and runtime support it. Otherwise keep `try` / `finally` explicit."],[496,"Use `bind()` when a callback will run later but should keep the current store."],[1014,"Use `createTimeoutSignal()` for a scope of related operations."],[1005,"Use `createTimeoutSignal()` when you need to pass one deadline signal across several calls."],[621,"Use `fetchSafe()` when you need the raw response and `fetchJsonSafe()` when success means \"valid JSON body\"."],[687,"Use `forEach()` or `mapAsyncLimit()` so the iterable can stream and cancellation can stop the work early."],[684,"Use `forEach()` when order and backpressure matter mo